DIAGNOSTICS
  E0290: `@fk`/`@no_fk` on `note` — only a forward to-one relation (which owns the `note_id` FK column) can carry one
  E0292: `both` carries both `@fk` and `@no_fk` — an FK is either opted in or out, not both
  E0293: `set_null` on required relation `hard` — make it optional (`hard: Org?`) for the FK to null it
SCHEMA
model Org  table=org
  id: Id
  name: text
model Order  table=order
  id: Id
  org: -> Org  fk=org_id
  note: text
  owner: -> Org?  fk=owner_id
  both: -> Org  fk=both_id
  hard: -> Org  fk=hard_id
